---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
import Testimonial from '../components/Testimonial.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Zero Fluff - AI Implementation That Works"
  description="Straight-talking AI consultancy helping small businesses implement AI that actually works. No jargon, no fluff, just results."
>
  <!-- Section 1: Hero (no .reveal -- visible immediately) -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow stack">
      <h1>AI Implementation That Actually Works</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted">
        I help small businesses use AI to save time, cut costs, and get more done.
        No jargon, no fifty-page strategy decks. Just practical tools and automations
        that fit into the way you already work.
      </p>
      <div>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Let's Talk</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Pain Points -->
  <section class="section reveal" style="background-color: var(--color-border);">
    <div class="container stack-lg">
      <div class="narrow stack">
        <h2>Sound familiar?</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">Most small businesses hit the same walls when it comes to AI. You're not alone.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card stack">
          <h3>You've seen the hype but don't know where to start</h3>
          <p>
            Every other LinkedIn post promises AI will change everything. But when you sit down
            to figure out what it actually means for your business, it's overwhelming. You don't
            need a revolution -- you need a clear first step.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card stack">
          <h3>You tried ChatGPT but it didn't stick</h3>
          <p>
            You played around with it, maybe got some decent results, but it never became
            part of how you work. The gap between a clever chatbot and a real business tool
            is bigger than anyone tells you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card stack">
          <h3>You're worried about wasting money</h3>
          <p>
            You've heard the horror stories -- expensive consultants, flashy demos, then nothing
            that actually works. You want to invest, but not blindly. Fair enough. That's exactly
            the right instinct.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Services Summary -->
  <section class="section reveal">
    <div class="container stack-lg">
      <div class="narrow stack">
        <h2>What I Do</h2>
        <p class="text-lg">
          I build AI-powered tools and automations that solve specific problems in your business.
          Not theory. Not advice. Working systems you can use from day one.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="card stack">
          <h3>AI Workflow Automation</h3>
          <p>
            Those repetitive tasks eating up your team's time? I automate them. Data entry,
            report generation, email sorting, invoice processing -- if a human is doing it
            on autopilot, a machine should be doing it instead.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card stack">
          <h3>Hands-On Implementation</h3>
          <p>
            I don't hand you a strategy document and wish you luck. I build the thing,
            test it, deploy it, and make sure it works. You get a working system,
            not a PowerPoint.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card stack">
          <h3>Ongoing Support</h3>
          <p>
            AI tools need looking after. Models change, your business evolves, things break.
            I stick around to keep everything running smoothly and adapt it as you grow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="narrow">
        <p><a href="/services">See everything I offer &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Testimonials -->
  <!-- Placeholder testimonials -- replace with real ones -->
  <section class="section reveal" style="background-color: var(--color-border);">
    <div class="container stack-lg">
      <div class="narrow stack">
        <h2>What People Say</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <Testimonial
          quote="Andy automated our weekly reporting and saved us about 8 hours a week. No fuss, no jargon -- he just got on with it and it worked from day one."
          name="Sarah Mitchell"
          role="Operations Director"
          company="Apex Logistics"
        />
        <Testimonial
          quote="I'd wasted months trying to figure out AI on my own. Andy sat down with me, understood my business in an hour, and built exactly what I needed. I finally get what AI can actually do for us."
          name="James Cooper"
          role="Founder"
          company="Bright Path Digital"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: CTA -->
  <CTA />

  <!-- Structured Data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Zero Fluff",
    "description": "Straight-talking AI consultancy for small businesses",
    "url": "https://zerofluff.co.uk",
    "address": {
      "@type": "PostalAddress",
      "addressLocality": "Totnes",
      "addressRegion": "Devon",
      "addressCountry": "GB"
    },
    "founder": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Andy Doyle"
    },
    "areaServed": "GB",
    "serviceType": ["AI Implementation", "AI Consultancy", "Business Automation"]
  })} />
</BaseLayout>
